@startuml 18-petri-net-marking
title PetriNet + PackedKeyTable Marking Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "PetriNet (src/models/petri_net.rs)" {
  component "places: Vec<Place>" as PLACES
  component "transitions: Vec<Transition>" as TRANS
  component "arcs: Vec<Arc>" as ARCS
  component "initial_marking:\nPackedKeyTable<String, usize>" as IMARK
}

package "PackedKeyTable<K, V>\n(src/utils/dense_kernel.rs)" as PKT {
  component "keys: Vec<K>" as KEYS
  component "values: Vec<V>" as VALS
  component "hashes: Vec<u64>\n(fnv1a_64 indexed)" as HASHES
  component "DenseIndex\n(hash → dense slot)" as DIDX
}

package "Token firing algebra" {
  component "input_mask: u64\n(bit per input place)" as IMASK
  component "output_mask: u64\n(bit per output place)" as OMASK
  component "marking: u64\n(current token state)" as MWORD
  component "enabled = (marking & input_mask)\n         == input_mask" as ENABLED
  component "next = (marking & !input_mask)\n      | output_mask" as NEXT
}

PLACES --> IMASK : index → bit position
PLACES --> OMASK : index → bit position
IMARK  --> MWORD : deserialize to bitmask (fast path)
PKT    --> IMARK  : implements

IMASK --> ENABLED
MWORD --> ENABLED
ENABLED --> NEXT
OMASK --> NEXT

note bottom of PKT
  FNV-1a hash is the universal ID spine.
  Same structure used for Q-table keys,
  net markings, and hashed event IDs.
end note

@enduml
